the better confirmation of that which is True;

as, That
the World is Eternal, That God cannot have
while to look after theſe Inferiour things;

if there be more Worlds than one,
then they muſt either be of the ſame, or of a
divers Nature;

for this were needleſs, and would argue
an Improvidence, ſince one could have no
